DISPATCH-BATCHING discipline (gm-method, SKILL.md dispatch cluster): one block is the DEFAULT, the serial single dispatch is the drift. Independent verbs batch as a class -- N prd-add/prd-resolve/mutable-add, orient recall+codesearch, inspection Read/codesearch -- N Writes one block then N Reads one block; only a true data dependency (B reads A's response) forces separate turns. Two edges bound it: (1) two Edits to the SAME file in one block is NOT fan-out -- the first invalidates the file read-state so the rest fail 'File has been modified since read'; collapse same-file changes to one Edit/replace_all/whole-file Write, batch only across DIFFERENT files. (2) a long verb (browser, exec_js build, git_finalize) whose response is not ready on the Write+Read block gets the wait probe AND the re-Read in ONE block (until [ -f out/<verb>-<N>.json ]; sleep; done + Read together, or honor advertised busy_until), never a bare wait turn then a separate Read turn. Homogeneous fan-out responses are read all-N-in-one-block or spot-checked first+last (no ordering dependency). Witnessed: this-run audit found a 6-Edit same-file block where only the first applied, and long-verb wait-then-separate-Read round-trips.